    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Squeezed Out</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Frederick J Geiersbach letter about Mar 25 article on computerized music in Broadway musicals</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I can appreciate why my colleague Peter Hoopes used this technology for our school production. The article notes the difficulty in locating players for such performances: ''try finding a harpist at a small boarding school.'' At St. Andrew's we do have a harp program. The main obstacles to including a harpist for ''Annie Get Your Gun'' was the small size of the pit and the difficulty of lowering the instrument through the stage floor.</p>
        <p>Frederick J. Geiersbach  Middletown, Del.</p>
        <p>The writer is director of instrumental music at St. Andrew's School.</p>
      </block>
